  "text": "We report here the two alternative semantics proposed in [CITATION_1] for parallel Sagas, namely the na\u00efve and revised versions. The main difference between the two semantics is that the latter allows the interruption of flow executions when a transaction fails. The set of parallel Sagas is given by the following grammar:",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "7055151"
